Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: 11:43 am case called. Defendant Alexander Matthew Stanelle in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PSI received by counsel. Attorney Zamzow states correction on record. DA Blader states no material corrections or errors. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Zamzow. Statement by Defendant. Statement by Court prior to sentencing.  Court sentences the defendant to: 7 years Wisconsin State Prison to be served as: 3 1/2 years Initial Confinement & 3 1/2 years Extended Supervision. Cocurrent to any other sentence. CONDITIONS OF ES:  AODA and follow through, Maintain absolute sobriety, not to be on the premises of any bars, defendant is not to possess nor ingest any controlled substances not prescribed by a treating physician. Restitution in the amount of $5,536.15, joint and several with Katrina Gruber and Nicholis Frost. To be paid first to deductible of church, then to insurer. No Contact with Katrina Gruber and/or Nicholis Frost. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Restitution and costs to be paid through 25% of inmate earnings during initial confinement and balance paid during extended supervision. Terms of Agent. Court finds the defendant eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program and eligible for Substance Abuse Program. DNA surcharge and sample to be provided. Court admonished defendant regarding expungement. Appeal Rights Given.

10:56 am case called. Defendant Alexander Matthew Stanelle in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow.  Defendant Alexander Matthew Stanelle in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by DA Blader agreement reached, preliminary hearing needs to be addressed, info filed, plea taken and PSI requested. Court has read the complaint, finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Zamzow confirms receipt and waives formal reading.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismissed outright the repeater enhancer. Court adjourns sentencing and orders a PSI to be prepared.   Court hears victim statement.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 10, 2016 at 11:15 am.
